#. type: Title =
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Software tools"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:5
msgid "Review software tools used in biodiversity informatics"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:7
msgid "During the Biodiversity Data Mobilization course activities, we’ll demonstrate and work with many different software tools related to data digitization, data quality and transformation. You probably already use several of them in your daily work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:9
msgid "Community trainers, mentors and former course participants have compiled a list with information about biodiversity informatics software tools. It provides links for their main websites, a key facts and a summary of strong and weak points."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:11
msgid "Download xref:attachment$Software-database-EN.xlsx[Software-database-EN.xlsx,opts=download]. (23 KB)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:15
msgid "When analysing biodiversity software that you have not used before, you need to consider how you would adapt it for your purposes.  You will find below a list with which you can start your evaluation.  They are inspired by the chapter “characteristics of a good database solution” of the GBIF manual https://www.gbif.org/document/80574/initiating-a-collection-digitisation-project[_Initiating a Digitisation Project_^]:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Price*: One of the most determining factors.\n"
"Beware of other costs beyond the price of the software license, such as hardware needed to run it, maintenance, upgrades, and the expertise to run it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Functionality*: You need to have clarity on what do you expect the software to achieve, and make sure it does it efficiently.\n"
"Do not get distracted by additional functionality that can make the software more complex unnecessarily.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Stability*: Some solutions have been in the market for long and are supported by solid institutions or companies are more likely to be bug-free and/or have good systems in place to solve any issues arising.\n"
"It will also make more likely to be updated and ported to more modern operating systems.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Scalability*: Some software performs very well when demoed out-of-the-box, but its  performance degrades after some time or when using them with larger amounts of data or when several users access it simultaneously.\n"
"Check the opinions of other users online.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Integration*: Make sure that the software accepts and produces the data formats that you use and need.\n"
"Data transformation is a time consuming task.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Language support*: it is essential that everyone using the software can understand its interface, and the documentation that will make possible its use.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Documentation and technical support*: make sure to explore the existing documentation and support mechanisms.\n"
"You can be sure that at some point you will need it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/foundations/modules/ROOT/pages/foundations-software.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Learning curve*: Some software may require specific training to learn how to use it, while others are more intuitive and can be learned while using them, supported by in-line help systems.\n"
msgstr ""

